cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the functionality of Natural Language Processing (NLP) systems in dealing with linguistic modality, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the implementation of multi-layered approaches for learning, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The review of logical approaches employed by NLP systems falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Lastly, the discussion of current research and futurology is related to neural networks (cs.NE).
